Spec: Agent Skills Command
Purpose:
  Deploy SpecDD Agent Skills into user or project Agent Skills directories.

Structure:
  ./agentskills.ts: Agent Skills command implementation.
  ./agentskills.test.ts: Agent Skills command tests.

Owns:
  ./agentskills.ts
  ./agentskills.test.ts

References:
  ../container.sdd
  ../services/agentskills/service.sdd

Must:
  Expose a factory for the agentskills command group.
  Receive an @AgentSkillsCommandContainer dependency object.
  Set concise command descriptions for help output.
  Expose a deploy subcommand.
  Accept an optional target path argument on deploy.
  Resolve a missing target path to the current working directory.
  Resolve a relative target path against the current working directory.
  Pass an absolute target path through as the target root directory.
  Accept a user-home deploy option.
  Resolve the user-home deploy option to the current user's home directory.
  Reject a target path when the user-home deploy option is set.
  Accept an optional release version option.
  Default the release version to latest.
  Include the project copyright notice in help output.
  Include SpecDD framework and CLI project help links in help output.
  Call @AgentSkills.deploy with the resolved target root directory and release version.
  Support construction by @Container.

Must not:
  Construct application services.
  Download, verify, or apply Agent Skills releases directly.
  Implement the CLI entrypoint.

Depends on:
  commander
  @Container
  @AgentSkills
  Node.js path handling
  Node.js home directory handling

Exposes:
  @createAgentSkillsCommand
  @resolveAgentSkillsDeployTargetPath
  @AgentSkillsDeployTargetConflictError

Accepts:
  optional target path
  optional user-home option
  optional release version

Returns:
  commander @Command
